.TH HALFEMPTY 1 "2026-06-20" "halfempty 0.40" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
halfempty \- fast, parallel file bisection / test-case minimizer
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B halfempty
.RI [ OPTION ...]
.I SCRIPT INPUTFILE
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B halfempty
reduces a large input file to a minimal one that still satisfies a test, by
running a lazy, parallel bisection.
.I SCRIPT
is an executable that reads a candidate input and exits successfully while the
input is still "interesting" (for example, still reproduces a bug);
.I INPUTFILE
is the file to minimize.
.PP
Unlike source-aware reducers such as
.BR cvise (1)
and
.BR creduce (1),
halfempty treats the input as an opaque byte stream, so it can minimize any
file \(em source, binary blobs, ROMs, crash inputs, fuzzer output \(em and
parallelizes aggressively for speed.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-o ", " \-\-output =\fIFILENAME\fR
Location to store the minimized output (default: halfempty.out).
.TP
.B \-\-stable
Re-run strategies until the result is stable.
.TP
.B \-\-continue
Do not exit; keep trying until interrupted.
.TP
.B \-\-noverify
Do not verify that the original input is interesting (not recommended).
.TP
.B \-\-monitor
Monitor progress in a web browser.
.TP
.B \-\-gen\-intermediate
Generate intermediate (reduced) files while processing.
.TP
.B \-\-line\-buffered
Ensure standard output is only line buffered.
.TP
.BR \-q ", " \-\-quiet
Minimize all messages; print only errors.
.TP
.BR \-h ", " \-\-help
Show help options.
.PP
Further option groups are available via
.BR \-\-help\-all ", " \-\-help\-threads ", " \-\-help\-process ", " \-\-help\-bisect ", "
and
.BR \-\-help\-zero .
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR cvise (1),
.BR creduce (1),
.BR picire (1)
